<br>
- Kelp <p><font face="arial" size="-1" color="#006666">
A mermaid found a swimming lad,<br>
Picked him for her own,<BR>
Pressed her body to his body,<BR>
Laughed; and plunging down<BR>
Forgot in cruel happiness<BR>
That even lovers drown.<BR>
<BR>
- W.B. Yeats
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 289<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/21/02 12:16:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> It's still on monkly-business.com ..</span><hr size=1> .. in the guides section, but I haven't updated it in a long time (Mo is Bjond, btw <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  I have a bunch of mostly minor corrections to add to it.  It only covers the TLC points for the Iksar shackle quests.  The epic parts also TLC starting around level 10 or so for the qeynos quests.<br>
<br>
If you want to do these quests for yourself, you'll pretty much need to decide between epic or shackle.  The TLCs are such that you can do one for yourself, but likely not both.  You can always buy the parts, though.  They're all tradable, even the epic parts. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
<i>"I will gladly pay you Tuesday for Sushi today!"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usisterkelp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sister Kelp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/21/02 5:39:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's still on monkly-business.com ..</span><hr size=1> Thanks Bjond.<br>
<br>
Would it be possible to do both shackles and epic if I spent a lot of time running around between kunark and antonica gathering pieces and then handed in the shackle parts once I fix my Cabilis faction? I'm 15th now, so I think I've probably already trivialed some of the first shackle pieces. I want to do both, damnit! <p><font face="arial" size="-1" color="#006666">
A mermaid found a swimming lad,<br>
Picked him for her own,<BR>
Pressed her body to his body,<BR>
Laughed; and plunging down<BR>
Forgot in cruel happiness<BR>
That even lovers drown.<BR>
<BR>
- W.B. Yeats
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarkitip.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkitip</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 298<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/21/02 6:36:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's still on monkly-business.com ..</span><hr size=1> Well...<br>
<br>
If you didn't already gather the putrid rib bones, you've hit TLC at 15th. Unless the putrid skellies at the South Karana camp are higher level.<br>
Yes it would be possible to do both, it would just be as extreme a pain in the ass as you're probably imagining it to be.<br>
You're already talking insanely boring camps (and I do mean insanely boring) for the headbands. Then the good ol' Raster camp, etc. <br>
If you're into punishment though... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usisterkelp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sister Kelp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/21/02 6:43:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's still on monkly-business.com ..</span><hr size=1> I did the rib bones last night at 13th, and even then a few of the putrids spawned green. I was scared :)<br>
<br>
I've made up a checklist of all the stuff I'll need for my sashes/headbands, so I can plan ahead to get the stuff I need. I've just been reading the shackle guides though and I can see that it will be a major pain in the ass to do them with TLC in place. <p><font face="arial" size="-1" color="#006666">
A mermaid found a swimming lad,<br>
Picked him for her own,<BR>
Pressed her body to his body,<BR>
Laughed; and plunging down<BR>
Forgot in cruel happiness<BR>
That even lovers drown.<BR>
<BR>
- W.B. Yeats
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarkitip.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkitip</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/22/02 12:23:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's still on monkly-business.com ..</span><hr size=1> Don't worry about the gnoll skins, they don't trivial.<br>
Granex Drah was still light blue when I went after him in my early 20s.<br>
I'm hoping Phido is still light blue... him and Grisok are supposed to be around 23rd.<br>
Ekeros is supposed to be about 25th, but he spawned green once for me at 30th. Bring a group for this one.<br>
Skull of Jhen'Tra is really easy to get, did this one in my late 20s.. probably 26th or so. Only problem is getting feared and bringing 5 gnoll shamans back... talk about a pain timing that FD.<br>
<br>
Befallen is my worst memory of it. I think I went in around 26th. Amiaz spawns pretty quickly, but the Thaumaturgist can take awhile.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 295<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/22/02 11:25:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I did all of the RoTL ..</span><hr size=1> .. and most of the shackle on FV before I moved Bjond to SH and finished his epic and shackles there.  The worst parts are the low level shackle spawns by far.  If you can get those out of the way, you can easily purchase any TLC'd epic parts.  The ribs are the worst ones, since they TLC low.<br>
<br>
I solo'd Ekeros in Najena at 27, 28, and 29 with Bjond.  Definitely one of the more fun low level solo encounters for a monk.  However, my guess is that solo'ing him will not be possible for those that have not solo'd at higher levels -- splitting and killing him definitely require more advanced monk skills (need your patience skill max'd out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br>
<br>
This is pretty much the gear I had on Bjond at the time I did Ekeros: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68059">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...?num=68059</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> (click the Bjond.21 alternate profile to see what he looked like then as opposed to now).  I think he had two PSU's and 6/65 rings for Ekeros instead of what Bjond.21 shows, but that's about it.  You can do all the RotLC fights solo even with TLC and boot-strap gear.  Same thing for shackles.<br>
<br>
edit: your goal of solo'ing all the parts to both IS possible, just long and hard.  You'll have to do a ton of running around.  Help from a tracker for loio and warsliks will reduce hunting time for courier and brutling to a minute fraction of the time you'll spend without a tracker helping. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
<i>"I will gladly pay you Tuesday for Sushi today!"</i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/22/02 11:29:56 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarkitip.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkitip</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 301<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/22/02 10:50:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did all of the RoTL ..</span><hr size=1> The only tough part of the Ekeros section is if the Dark Elf is up in the adjacent room. The mages are easy as hell but if he's around it makes a split much more difficult with all the key juggling and whatnot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umuklestikk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mukle Stikk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/23/02 12:17:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I did all of the RoTL ..</span><hr size=1> Did they nerf Bro Z and Gwan? <br>
<br>
People still do the monk epic the old way?<br>
<br>
Get the 2 pipes and you have your epic.  Kill Bro Z,<br>
get your RotWF then get 2 l33t groups and go rape the elemental masters.  Even Xenevorash is a wuss.<br>
<br>
I heard of one monk on prexus doing his whole epic in one day after he had both of his pipes.<br>
<br>
 <p>Mukle Stikk<BR>
Grandmaster (retired)<BR>
<BR>

<img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/deadpool/muklesig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 298<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/23/02 12:55:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> LOL Mukle</span><hr size=1> Your comment above is pretty rude -- uh, you do know that you're talking to a level 15 monk right?  It's like telling a 16yr-old out to buy first car &quot;I've got a Ferrari.  It rocks.  You should get one, too.&quot;  Also, you show a number of misconceptions that make me wonder if you've ever killed Brother Z or the monk epic masters yourself.<br>
<br>
Z drops robe maybe 1 in 5 times now (and it's Qwin, not Gwan, as the other robe source).  It's pretty common to go kill him and he doesn't drop anything.  He's not a common spawn and you can't use the 2HB trick anymore.  Forcibly spawning him can often take a full day.  Also, you don't need two groups for the final 4 fights.  You can do the first 3 fights with 2-4 people and the last one in loio only needs 4-6.  I've done this 4-5 times recently on SH.  Time to do all 4 fights runs 2-4H.<br>
<br>
Even on servers with a plethora of 60s, most monks quest for the RotLC rather than kill for it.  Not only is it traditional, but most folks are a bit irked when someone asks them for help on things that they can easily solo.  Save up your &quot;camp this for me&quot; favors for things that really need help! <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
<i>"I will gladly pay you Tuesday for Sushi today!"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarkitip.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkitip</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 302<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/23/02 4:46:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LOL Mukle</span><hr size=1> It's also generally considered bad form to kill Qwinn because of the silliness of his spawning. Plus he's more badass than Zephyl. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=2372.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2372.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2372.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.threadControl?topicID=2372.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2372.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2372.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></t